1
00:00:01,902 --> 00:00:05,070
   [sigh] I just wanted everything
   to be perfect.

2
00:00:05,172 --> 00:00:07,506
        I mean, this was
        a BIG DEAL!

3
00:00:07,608 --> 00:00:09,741
    But when Discord insists
    on being involved...

4
00:00:09,843 --> 00:00:11,576
       Regardless of what
        Spike might say,

5
00:00:11,678 --> 00:00:13,679
       that little dragon
       BEGGED me to help.

6
00:00:13,781 --> 00:00:16,648
   And let me tell you, he
   can cause plenty of chaos

7
00:00:16,750 --> 00:00:18,917
        all on his
        purple lonesome!

8
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:22,421
  I PRIDE myself on baking
  under pressure but I just...

9
00:00:22,523 --> 00:00:23,723
           Oh, dear.

10
00:00:24,325 --> 00:00:27,326
You'd think we'd be used to
stuff like this in Ponyville.

11
00:00:27,528 --> 00:00:29,228
                    I still have
                    nightmares.

12
00:00:29,930 --> 00:00:32,364
        It seemed simple
        when it started..

13
00:00:34,536 --> 00:00:38,237
      Oh! It's BEAUTIFUL!

14
00:00:38,339 --> 00:00:39,505
             Eeyup!

15
00:00:41,208 --> 00:00:41,841
                           NOPE!

16
00:00:41,943 --> 00:00:43,509
     I'm not gonna EAT it!

17
00:00:43,911 --> 00:00:44,777
     Eat what?

18
00:00:47,214 --> 00:00:47,980
                     What is it!

19
00:00:48,082 --> 00:00:49,281
I wanna see!

20
00:00:49,383 --> 00:00:50,216
                Nope!

21
00:00:50,318 --> 00:00:51,417
                        Why not?

22
00:00:51,519 --> 00:00:53,319
        Because you have
        a big mouth.

23
00:00:53,421 --> 00:00:54,486
                          ME?

24
00:00:54,988 --> 00:00:56,722
     I keep TONS
     of secrets!

25
00:00:56,824 --> 00:00:59,459
Like Fluttershy's
secret fear of clowns,

26
00:00:59,561 --> 00:01:03,696
or that time I caught Twilight
sleeptrotting through town.

27
00:01:03,798 --> 00:01:07,199
Oh, and did you know that
Octavia went on a date

28
00:01:07,301 --> 00:01:12,238
with Bulk Biceps? Talk about
an odd couple! I heard that...

29
00:01:12,540 --> 00:01:15,074
Oh. All right,
point taken.

30
00:01:15,276 --> 00:01:16,842
But we're
pals, right?

31
00:01:16,944 --> 00:01:18,944
       COMRADES. AMIGOS!

32
00:01:19,346 --> 00:01:20,912
            COME ON!

33
00:01:23,117 --> 00:01:25,885
               ♪♪

34
00:01:25,987 --> 00:01:27,186
             [gasp]

35
00:01:27,288 --> 00:01:31,223
    BIG MAC IS GOING TO
    PROPOSE TO SUGAR BELLE?

36
00:01:31,325 --> 00:01:33,926
      [echo] SUGAR BELLE!
       SUGAR BELLE!

37
00:02:14,735 --> 00:02:17,536
  Of course, Big Mac asked ME
  to help with his proposal;

38
00:02:17,638 --> 00:02:19,805
     I'm the most romantic
     dragon I know.

39
00:02:20,007 --> 00:02:23,174
    Oh! It really is a curse
    having infinite powers.

40
00:02:23,276 --> 00:02:24,976
Everypony's
always asking you

41
00:02:25,078 --> 00:02:26,645
to move a couch

42
00:02:26,747 --> 00:02:29,214
or help with
a proposal.

43
00:02:30,818 --> 00:02:32,818
         Spill it!
         EVERY detail!

44
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:34,052
Don't leave
anything out!

45
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:36,755
           Agh! Do we have to
           hear ALL the details?

46
00:02:36,857 --> 00:02:39,891
                 Is that like, a
                 <i>friend</i> thing?

47
00:02:40,093 --> 00:02:42,160
[sigh] Eyup.

48
00:02:42,362 --> 00:02:43,628
             [zap]

49
00:02:45,466 --> 00:02:50,502
    I don't talk much so I
    want to SHOW Sugar Belle

50
00:02:50,604 --> 00:02:54,338
         how committed
         I am. First...

51
00:02:54,739 --> 00:02:55,485
            [clunk]

52
00:02:57,610 --> 00:02:59,943
 [gasp] You're making a picnic table
 that matches the shelf

53
00:03:00,045 --> 00:03:01,078
       you made Sugar
       Belle for her shop

54
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:01,946
         when you had a
         crush on her

55
00:03:02,048 --> 00:03:03,214
       and you're setting
       up a romantic meal

56
00:03:03,316 --> 00:03:04,783
       overlooking Sweet
       Apple Acres!?

57
00:03:04,885 --> 00:03:05,785
             Eyup!

58
00:03:05,987 --> 00:03:07,953
                Uh. How did you
                figure that out?

59
00:03:08,255 --> 00:03:09,521
       If you were a
       hopeless romantic,

60
00:03:09,623 --> 00:03:11,556
    you'd know that was the
    only logical choice.

61
00:03:11,858 --> 00:03:13,358
Then...

62
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:16,027
♪♪

63
00:03:16,129 --> 00:03:18,429
     You painted apples to
     leave around Ponyville

64
00:03:18,531 --> 00:03:20,031
      with little riddles
      tied to the stem

65
00:03:20,133 --> 00:03:22,067
      that will lead her
      up here to meet you?

66
00:03:22,169 --> 00:03:23,068
   Eyup.

67
00:03:23,170 --> 00:03:24,469
                      Seriously?

68
00:03:24,571 --> 00:03:26,938
            Now...
            -Yeah--

69
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:30,141
       Oh, I know! You need a
       giant rhino named Delores

70
00:03:30,243 --> 00:03:33,011
         who can knit a romantic
         sweater for two!

71
00:03:33,113 --> 00:03:35,647
          Uh... Nope.

72
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:37,016
             [snap]

73
00:03:37,318 --> 00:03:40,885
Come on! He needs food for
the picnic. That was a gimme.

74
00:03:42,289 --> 00:03:44,089
                    I do not get
                    this game.

75
00:03:44,391 --> 00:03:45,991
         OK. You finish
         your table...

76
00:03:46,093 --> 00:03:47,459
     I'll pick up whatever
     you need to eat

77
00:03:47,561 --> 00:03:49,528
    and Discord will put
    all the apples in place.

78
00:03:49,630 --> 00:03:50,529
                     I will?

79
00:03:50,631 --> 00:03:51,430
   Eeyup!

80
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:56,367
   ♪♪

81
00:03:56,469 --> 00:03:57,502
                     [zap]

82
00:03:58,405 --> 00:03:59,871
           [munching]

83
00:04:00,473 --> 00:04:02,439
        [zap]
       [chicken squawks]

84
00:04:02,876 --> 00:04:05,043
♪♪

85
00:04:05,145 --> 00:04:08,580
   From the Sugarcube Corner,
   look for your next clue.

86
00:04:08,682 --> 00:04:11,216
        Red, delicious,
        sweet like you.

87
00:04:11,318 --> 00:04:13,618
        Find it; you'll
        know what to do...?

88
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:14,720
          Ugh.

89
00:04:15,322 --> 00:04:17,422
       He should stick
       to bucking apples.

90
00:04:17,624 --> 00:04:19,724
         Sugar Belle's
         gonna love it!

91
00:04:19,826 --> 00:04:26,431
♪♪

92
00:04:26,533 --> 00:04:27,299
I'll get the food.

93
00:04:27,401 --> 00:04:29,367
How long will it take you
to place all the apples?

94
00:04:29,569 --> 00:04:30,402
[zap]

95
00:04:30,804 --> 00:04:33,338
    Are you sure you put
    them in the right spots?

96
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:35,707
     Those terrible
     riddles on the apples

97
00:04:35,809 --> 00:04:38,076
        were VERY clear
        on the location.

98
00:04:38,178 --> 00:04:40,245
     I'm sure that they
     were placed properly.

99
00:04:41,715 --> 00:04:44,916
                I-I think. Maybe.
                Does it matter?

100
00:04:46,253 --> 00:04:49,087
       Oh, OK fine! I'll
       double check.

101
00:04:49,189 --> 00:04:49,954
          [door opens]

102
00:04:53,794 --> 00:04:56,561
She didn't see the apple!
What are we gonna do!?

103
00:04:56,663 --> 00:04:58,864
             Well, we could just
             GIVE it to her.

104
00:04:58,966 --> 00:05:01,566
That's not romantic! She
needs to discover it.

105
00:05:01,868 --> 00:05:03,802
                 Don't be such a
                 drama dragon.

106
00:05:03,904 --> 00:05:06,771
        I've precipitated liquid
        cocoa on Equestria,

107
00:05:06,873 --> 00:05:08,974
          and herded long-limbed
          Leporidae;

108
00:05:09,076 --> 00:05:12,978
            I can certainly make
            a pony SEE an apple.

109
00:05:13,047 --> 00:05:13,913
             [zap]

110
00:05:14,315 --> 00:05:15,214
             [sigh]

111
00:05:15,316 --> 00:05:16,748
               ♪♪

112
00:05:16,850 --> 00:05:17,616
             [ding]

113
00:05:17,718 --> 00:05:19,284
♪♪

114
00:05:19,386 --> 00:05:21,752
    Hey Mrs. Cake. I need
    to pick up a few things.

115
00:05:22,389 --> 00:05:24,155
      Oh, I'm afraid
      you'll have to wait.

116
00:05:24,257 --> 00:05:25,824
         I'm a bit busy
         at the moment!

117
00:05:25,926 --> 00:05:28,493
     Oh, is this sour
     cream or sweet cream?

118
00:05:30,697 --> 00:05:32,764
         Oh, it's kind
         of important...

119
00:05:32,966 --> 00:05:35,033
   Maybe I could take some
   of these off your hooves?

120
00:05:35,435 --> 00:05:39,104
     NO! Those are for...
    something important too!

121
00:05:39,306 --> 00:05:41,940
All of them? There's...
one, two, three, four..

122
00:05:42,042 --> 00:05:44,843
       Twenty-ONE and
       yes all of them.

123
00:05:44,945 --> 00:05:46,545
Who needs twenty-one
 desserts?

124
00:05:46,647 --> 00:05:49,981
        I can't tell you! It's
        a secret. Come by later.

125
00:05:50,083 --> 00:05:51,350
Later won't work!

126
00:05:51,852 --> 00:05:52,751
                 Why not?

127
00:05:52,853 --> 00:05:54,954
       I can't tell you!
       It's a secret.

128
00:05:55,356 --> 00:05:57,088
       Put the vanilla in
       the... with the...

129
00:05:57,190 --> 00:06:00,792
       UGH! Did somepony
       else bake these?

130
00:06:01,094 --> 00:06:03,094
   No. Why..?

131
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:04,195
                      No reason..

132
00:06:04,397 --> 00:06:08,867
      <i> ♪ [gentle music] ♪</i>

133
00:06:08,969 --> 00:06:09,701
                     [zap]

134
00:06:09,803 --> 00:06:10,469
             [pop]

135
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:12,236
                     [zap]

136
00:06:14,475 --> 00:06:16,775
              Thank you!
              These are perfect!

137
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:20,712
       [zap]

138
00:06:22,816 --> 00:06:24,349
       You know, if she's
       too busy to read

139
00:06:24,451 --> 00:06:26,851
         the horribly
         written clues..

140
00:06:26,953 --> 00:06:28,653
        Maybe you should
         just tell her.

141
00:06:28,855 --> 00:06:29,687
             [snap]

142
00:06:30,257 --> 00:06:32,123
          [crunching]

143
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:33,392
            [squeak]

144
00:06:33,894 --> 00:06:34,659
             [snap]

145
00:06:35,862 --> 00:06:36,862
             [zap]

146
00:06:37,064 --> 00:06:38,530
        [squeaky sounds]

147
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:43,368
[gravelly voice]
Listen up, each of
you has a job to do.

148
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:44,936
Take a look at
your stems.

149
00:06:45,138 --> 00:06:47,305
          [squeaking]

150
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:48,707
    Well, tell me about it.

151
00:06:48,809 --> 00:06:51,543
   But regardless, go to your
    designated location,

152
00:06:51,645 --> 00:06:55,580
   deliver your messages and
   make me proud! Dismissed!

153
00:06:56,082 --> 00:06:58,316
          [squeaking]

154
00:06:58,418 --> 00:06:59,284
             [zap]

155
00:06:59,386 --> 00:07:02,187
    Oh. I just have to say Big
    Mac is REALLY lucky

156
00:07:02,289 --> 00:07:03,755
    to have me as a friend.

157
00:07:03,857 --> 00:07:09,127
♪♪

158
00:07:09,229 --> 00:07:13,365
    [nervous voice] OK... One
    down. Twenty to go.

159
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:15,667
            THEN I can help you.

160
00:07:16,469 --> 00:07:18,269
Maybe I can help YOU!

161
00:07:19,606 --> 00:07:21,172
     Delivering parchments
       is my thing!

162
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:23,108
        A little dragon
       breath and FWOOSH!

163
00:07:23,210 --> 00:07:25,210
    We "deliver" each scroll
     into each dessert!

164
00:07:25,312 --> 00:07:26,644
        Then you can
        help me! Watch!

165
00:07:26,746 --> 00:07:27,378
                   Whoa!

166
00:07:28,615 --> 00:07:29,647
          [whoosh]

167
00:07:29,749 --> 00:07:30,849
          <i> ♪ TA-DA! ♪</i>

168
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:33,883
       [crackling flames]

169
00:07:35,022 --> 00:07:37,355
      [screaming outside]

170
00:07:38,025 --> 00:07:40,358
       Hurry, there's no
       need to sneak,

171
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:43,094
       the next apple is
       at the boutique!

172
00:07:43,196 --> 00:07:45,063
          [screaming]

173
00:07:46,775 --> 00:07:47,575
         [squeak]

174
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:48,532
             [slam]

175
00:07:48,634 --> 00:07:50,935
At Twilight's
castle take a right.

176
00:07:51,037 --> 00:07:53,972
The next apple sits
in plain sight!

177
00:07:54,774 --> 00:07:55,941
          [screaming]

178
00:07:56,043 --> 00:07:58,043
             What in the blazes
              is going on?

179
00:07:58,545 --> 00:07:59,677
            Discord..

180
00:07:59,779 --> 00:08:00,545
             [zap]

181
00:08:02,949 --> 00:08:06,618
 Oh, are you finally finished?
 I've been done for a while.

182
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:09,686
           [screams]

183
00:08:11,224 --> 00:08:12,157
            [splat]

184
00:08:13,193 --> 00:08:15,126
         You know,
         thinking back,

185
00:08:15,228 --> 00:08:17,161
    I probably could have
    been clearer WHICH pony

186
00:08:17,263 --> 00:08:19,197
         to deliver the
         messages to.

187
00:08:19,399 --> 00:08:20,331
           Ya think?

188
00:08:21,735 --> 00:08:23,235
             [zap]

189
00:08:23,637 --> 00:08:26,104
      I sent them back to
      Sweet Apple Acres.

190
00:08:26,206 --> 00:08:29,708
     Apples are TERRIBLE
     at taking directions.

191
00:08:29,810 --> 00:08:32,377
    Couldn't even manage to
    stay in one location.

192
00:08:32,479 --> 00:08:37,582
   Now bananas... oh ho, are
   MUCH better at listening.

193
00:08:37,684 --> 00:08:38,917
         Sugar Belle:
        What's going on?

194
00:08:39,419 --> 00:08:40,986
                  Apples running
                  EVERYWHERE

195
00:08:41,088 --> 00:08:44,089
     and she didn't see the
     poem to get to the hilltop!?

196
00:08:44,191 --> 00:08:46,157
Getting her to the
hilltop is easy,

197
00:08:46,259 --> 00:08:49,227
and not seeing the poems
is actually a blessing

198
00:08:49,329 --> 00:08:50,895
when you think about it.

199
00:08:51,097 --> 00:08:52,730
             [zap]

200
00:08:55,002 --> 00:08:56,268
             [zap]

201
00:08:56,470 --> 00:08:59,037
     Why would you think
    sending FLAMING messages

202
00:08:59,139 --> 00:09:02,841
  into my desserts would work!?
  You've ruined all of them!

203
00:09:02,943 --> 00:09:05,343
          To be honest, I tasted
          some and burning them

204
00:09:05,445 --> 00:09:06,711
                 might have been
                 an improvement.

205
00:09:06,813 --> 00:09:08,747
  What? I NEVER!

206
00:09:08,850 --> 00:09:12,717
   -Big Mac: Spike?
-Oh! Hey there, Big Mac. I
 bet you're wondering what-

207
00:09:12,819 --> 00:09:13,585
          Sugar Belle!

208
00:09:14,087 --> 00:09:14,953
                  Big Mac?

209
00:09:15,055 --> 00:09:15,821
      [zap]

210
00:09:15,923 --> 00:09:17,322
            DISCORD?

211
00:09:17,824 --> 00:09:19,090
           Mrs. Cake!

212
00:09:19,192 --> 00:09:20,191
         What did I do!?

213
00:09:21,161 --> 00:09:21,960
Nothing.

214
00:09:22,062 --> 00:09:24,430
I thought we were just
saying each other's names!

215
00:09:24,932 --> 00:09:27,232
      Well, I guess this
      can't get any worse.

216
00:09:27,734 --> 00:09:29,034
     As the Lord of Chaos,

217
00:09:29,136 --> 00:09:31,102
    I'd advise against
    saying things like that.

218
00:09:31,204 --> 00:09:33,205
          [screaming]

219
00:09:33,307 --> 00:09:35,807
         It's coming!
        Save yourselves!

220
00:09:35,909 --> 00:09:37,142
           [booming]

221
00:09:37,244 --> 00:09:39,911
   [monster voice]
   SUGAR BELLE!

222
00:09:40,113 --> 00:09:42,117
           [crashing]

223
00:09:42,241 --> 00:09:45,841
      SUGAR BELLE!

224
00:09:49,189 --> 00:09:50,123
               ♪♪

225
00:09:50,224 --> 00:09:53,858
 We have a bit of a reputation
 for getting carried away.

226
00:09:54,061 --> 00:09:56,862
      Especially when
      romance is involved. Heh.

227
00:09:56,964 --> 00:09:58,663
      But that WASN'T
      the case with this.

228
00:09:58,765 --> 00:10:01,099
   We were just helping
   Sugar Belle with HER plan.

229
00:10:04,605 --> 00:10:07,572
        And the last one should
         just say, "Eyup."

230
00:10:08,977 --> 00:10:12,811
   Oo. Er. So you're saying you want
   to put each one of <i>those</i>

231
00:10:12,913 --> 00:10:14,446
       inside a dessert?

232
00:10:14,748 --> 00:10:17,248
Well, since Big Mac's plan to
send me a Hearts and Hooves Day

233
00:10:17,350 --> 00:10:19,885
   pie with a message
   inside didn't go so well,

234
00:10:20,087 --> 00:10:22,020
      I thought it'd be
      fun to do it right.

235
00:10:22,322 --> 00:10:25,624
    Aw! That's SO romantic!

236
00:10:26,126 --> 00:10:29,261
   He's a pony of few words;
   I love that about him!

237
00:10:29,363 --> 00:10:32,063
    So I thought I'd use as
    many words as possible

238
00:10:32,165 --> 00:10:35,334
     to propose to him!
     All he has to say is...

239
00:10:35,436 --> 00:10:40,338
EYUP! [giggle] I can't wait for you
to be a part of the family!

240
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,040
                You three played
                such a big part

241
00:10:42,142 --> 00:10:43,775
       in Big Mac and I
       getting together.

242
00:10:43,977 --> 00:10:45,543
       I'm glad you could
        help with this.

243
00:10:47,581 --> 00:10:49,648
   I-love-you-Big-Mac-Would-
   you-like-to-spend-

244
00:10:49,750 --> 00:10:52,651
the-rest-of-our-lives-together-
I-hope-you-say-eyup!

245
00:10:52,753 --> 00:10:55,320
      And each word has to
      go into a dessert!?

246
00:10:55,422 --> 00:10:58,689
 That's... one, two, three,
 four, five, six, seven...Whoa!

247
00:10:58,791 --> 00:11:00,325
             Twenty-one! I know!

248
00:11:01,027 --> 00:11:02,794
   Actually, it's twenty-two.

249
00:11:04,297 --> 00:11:06,164
     Mrs. Cake was kind
     enough to help me bake

250
00:11:06,266 --> 00:11:08,099
     ALL the apple-flavored
       treats I made

251
00:11:08,201 --> 00:11:10,436
    to get Big Mac to visit
     me in my old shop,

252
00:11:11,138 --> 00:11:12,937
        but THAT one has
        the invitation

253
00:11:13,039 --> 00:11:15,373
     for HIM to come HERE.

254
00:11:15,475 --> 00:11:18,910
     Oh, it's no bother! I
     DO love a challenge!

255
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:21,880
    Did I add the sugar to
    this one or to that one?

256
00:11:24,618 --> 00:11:28,519
I think I've seen her add sugar
to that bowl six times so far..

257
00:11:29,690 --> 00:11:31,724
       Now you three go
       deliver that pie!

258
00:11:32,526 --> 00:11:35,061
   I have to get some flowers
   to spruce the place up!

259
00:11:35,963 --> 00:11:38,930
     [gasp] Uh-oh! Spike and
      Discord are outside.

260
00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:40,366
       If they figure out
       what we're up to,

261
00:11:40,468 --> 00:11:43,501
 they'll spill the beans and I
  want this to be a surprise!

262
00:11:45,172 --> 00:11:45,871
          [door opens]

263
00:11:45,973 --> 00:11:49,674
♪♪

264
00:11:49,776 --> 00:11:51,776
              I don't think they
              suspect anything!

265
00:11:51,978 --> 00:11:52,978
Why would they suspect

266
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:54,713
that we're holding
an invitation pie

267
00:11:54,815 --> 00:11:57,516
and that Mrs. Cake is baking a
twenty-one-dessert proposal?

268
00:11:57,618 --> 00:12:00,285
   I CAN'T BELIEVE I'M GONNA
   HAVE A SISTER-IN-LAW!

269
00:12:00,387 --> 00:12:02,953
      Echo: Sister-in-law!
       Sister-in-law!

270
00:12:04,257 --> 00:12:05,224
  Shhh!

271
00:12:06,026 --> 00:12:08,259
This is our shot to make
up for all the trouble

272
00:12:08,361 --> 00:12:11,262
we caused when Big Mac first
asked Sugar Belle out!

273
00:12:11,364 --> 00:12:13,031
              We can't give away
              the surprise!

274
00:12:13,133 --> 00:12:14,599
                   You need to
                   play it cool!

275
00:12:14,801 --> 00:12:17,568
         Right, right.
        Uh, how's this?

276
00:12:18,672 --> 00:12:19,671
                  Better..?

277
00:12:19,873 --> 00:12:22,040
Come on! Let's go
find your brother!

278
00:12:24,477 --> 00:12:27,312
      Screwdriver... nope.

279
00:12:27,414 --> 00:12:32,317
♪♪

280
00:12:32,419 --> 00:12:33,551
            Big Mac?

281
00:12:34,755 --> 00:12:36,454
He ain't here!
Let's go!

282
00:12:36,556 --> 00:12:37,689
            Hold on..

283
00:12:38,091 --> 00:12:39,724
        That looks just
        like the shelf

284
00:12:39,826 --> 00:12:43,361
      Big Mac made for
      Sugar Belle! Weird...

285
00:12:43,463 --> 00:12:45,464
Maybe we should
wait here for him.

286
00:12:45,666 --> 00:12:47,332
He's bound to
show up soon!

287
00:12:47,634 --> 00:12:49,601
Y'know, when I'm
lookin' for something,

288
00:12:49,703 --> 00:12:53,405
 Granny says it's best to
 check the least likely place.

289
00:12:53,807 --> 00:12:54,539
            COME ON!

290
00:12:54,641 --> 00:12:56,875
      <i> ♪ [upbeat music] ♪</i>

291
00:12:56,977 --> 00:13:00,879
    <i> ♪ [slow-paced music] ♪</i>

292
00:13:00,981 --> 00:13:02,347
          Screwdriver!

293
00:13:03,216 --> 00:13:06,518
♪♪

294
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:07,819
            BIG MAC!

295
00:13:07,921 --> 00:13:08,687
            [crash]

296
00:13:08,789 --> 00:13:11,957
♪♪

297
00:13:12,659 --> 00:13:13,859
[door opens and closes]

298
00:13:14,161 --> 00:13:15,460
     <i> ♪ [peaceful music] ♪</i>

299
00:13:15,562 --> 00:13:20,231
♪♪

300
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,499
            BIG MAC!

301
00:13:26,473 --> 00:13:27,572
            BIG MAC!

302
00:13:27,674 --> 00:13:28,639
            [scream]

303
00:13:29,409 --> 00:13:30,075
              Agh!

304
00:13:32,879 --> 00:13:33,545
                    [slam]

305
00:13:33,647 --> 00:13:34,212
      [sigh]

306
00:13:35,916 --> 00:13:38,516
  How is Sugar Belle supposed
   to propose to Big Mac

307
00:13:38,618 --> 00:13:40,452
   if we can't even find him!?

308
00:13:41,454 --> 00:13:44,222
    Mrs. Cake isn't finished
    yet. We still have time.

309
00:13:44,324 --> 00:13:46,625
     Y'know, when I'm
     lookin' for somepony,

310
00:13:46,727 --> 00:13:49,561
    Granny says it's best to
    just stay in one place.

311
00:13:49,663 --> 00:13:51,396
              Let's head back to
              the farm and wait.

312
00:13:51,498 --> 00:13:53,264
                Big Mac is sure
                to show up soon!

313
00:13:54,768 --> 00:13:57,301
           Well, don't just
           stand there. Come on!

314
00:13:58,571 --> 00:14:00,004
          [squeaking]

315
00:14:00,106 --> 00:14:00,972
             [poof]

316
00:14:01,074 --> 00:14:02,640
      LOVE IS IN THE AIR!

317
00:14:04,877 --> 00:14:07,712
♪♪

318
00:14:07,814 --> 00:14:08,580
             Eyup.

319
00:14:08,682 --> 00:14:10,581
    [distant sheep bleating]

320
00:14:10,683 --> 00:14:11,983
           [tapping]

321
00:14:12,085 --> 00:14:13,084
         Eeeeeeeeeyup.

322
00:14:13,186 --> 00:14:17,187
          [chittering]

323
00:14:17,257 --> 00:14:20,458
    <i> ♪ [gentle solo flute] ♪</i>

324
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:25,029
               ♪♪

325
00:14:25,131 --> 00:14:25,964
Granny!

326
00:14:26,166 --> 00:14:27,198
                WHO GOES THERE?

327
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:29,134
        Granny, have you
        seen Big Mac?

328
00:14:29,236 --> 00:14:31,069
                Oh, hey there,
                little dumpling.

329
00:14:31,171 --> 00:14:34,472
              I jut had the most
              peculiar dream.

330
00:14:34,674 --> 00:14:35,440
That's nice, Granny,

331
00:14:35,542 --> 00:14:37,175
but we REALLY need to
find Big Mac, so...

332
00:14:37,277 --> 00:14:40,178
           It was about Grand
           Pear, only it wasn't..

333
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:43,214
   And we were in outer space
   on some kinda mission

334
00:14:43,316 --> 00:14:45,517
       to explore strange
        new worlds..

335
00:14:45,819 --> 00:14:47,952
            If we get stuck
            listening to Granny,

336
00:14:48,054 --> 00:14:49,755
                we'll never
                find Big Mac!

337
00:14:50,057 --> 00:14:54,092
   And Mud Briar was there,
   bein' as logical as ever,

338
00:14:54,194 --> 00:14:56,094
        but his ears was
        all pointy-like.

339
00:14:56,196 --> 00:14:59,230
   And then Discord showed up
    and... well... you know,

340
00:14:59,332 --> 00:15:00,932
         he was pretty
         much the same...

341
00:15:01,034 --> 00:15:02,300
      Once she gets going,

342
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:04,936
  there's nothing in Equestria
     that can stop her.

343
00:15:05,038 --> 00:15:08,807
        [loud thumping]

344
00:15:08,909 --> 00:15:10,141
      You sure about that?

345
00:15:10,243 --> 00:15:15,646
      [thumping continues]

346
00:15:16,348 --> 00:15:18,748
-Spike?
         -Oh, hey there,
          Big Mac.

347
00:15:19,085 --> 00:15:20,284
        I bet you're
        wondering what-

348
00:15:20,386 --> 00:15:21,152
          Sugar Belle!

349
00:15:21,454 --> 00:15:22,353
                  Big Mac?

350
00:15:22,455 --> 00:15:23,254
                  [zap]

351
00:15:23,456 --> 00:15:24,823
            DISCORD?

352
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:26,424
           Mrs. Cake!

353
00:15:26,526 --> 00:15:27,492
         What did I do!?

354
00:15:28,394 --> 00:15:30,628
Nothing. I thought
we were just saying

355
00:15:30,730 --> 00:15:31,897
each other's names!

356
00:15:32,399 --> 00:15:34,666
      Well, I guess this
      can't get any worse.

357
00:15:35,168 --> 00:15:36,534
As the Lord of Chaos,

358
00:15:36,636 --> 00:15:38,736
I'd advise against
saying things like that.

359
00:15:38,838 --> 00:15:40,738
          [screaming]

360
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:43,074
         It's coming!
        Save yourselves!

361
00:15:43,176 --> 00:15:45,777
        [loud thumping]

362
00:15:45,879 --> 00:15:48,513
        [monster voice]
        SUGAR BELLE!

363
00:15:50,283 --> 00:15:54,185
          SUGAR BELLE!

364
00:15:54,287 --> 00:15:55,620
            DISCORD!?

365
00:15:56,222 --> 00:15:58,490
Why does everypony
immediately assume

366
00:15:58,592 --> 00:16:00,425
that this has something
to do with me?

367
00:16:00,627 --> 00:16:03,094
    I love you, you love me,

368
00:16:03,196 --> 00:16:06,231
      our love will grow
      like an apple tree!

369
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:09,768
       So let me ask,
       will you marry me?

370
00:16:10,670 --> 00:16:11,670
            [splash]

371
00:16:11,772 --> 00:16:15,406
OK, but to be fair, the message
  DID get to Sugar Belle.

372
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:18,175
               ♪♪

373
00:16:21,414 --> 00:16:23,181
      This whole story is
      being twisted

374
00:16:23,283 --> 00:16:25,383
      to make it seem like
      it was all my fault!

375
00:16:25,685 --> 00:16:27,718
        Which it wasn't!

376
00:16:29,689 --> 00:16:32,557
       Wait. So you two were
       orchestrating a proposal?

377
00:16:32,759 --> 00:16:34,325
                 That's what I
                  was doing!

378
00:16:34,427 --> 00:16:36,026
Who are you
proposing to?

379
00:16:36,128 --> 00:16:37,228
Apple Bloom: Discord!

380
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:38,729
              ME?

381
00:16:39,566 --> 00:16:42,466
       I love you, I love
       you, I love you!

382
00:16:42,568 --> 00:16:43,834
          [snap] [zap]

383
00:16:43,936 --> 00:16:46,371
          [clattering]

384
00:16:46,473 --> 00:16:48,973
So the messages that
were in the desserts...

385
00:16:49,075 --> 00:16:51,910
             ..were Sugar Belle's
             proposal to Big Mac

386
00:16:52,012 --> 00:16:53,879
                before Spike set
               them on FIRE.

387
00:16:54,381 --> 00:16:57,348
Oh! So, I'm not the only
one who messes things up,

388
00:16:57,450 --> 00:17:00,752
am I, Mister <i>High</i>
and <i>Mighty</i> Dragon?

389
00:17:00,854 --> 00:17:02,287
      Hey! Those desserts
       were ruined

390
00:17:02,389 --> 00:17:03,955
          way before I
          ruined them!

391
00:17:04,057 --> 00:17:05,457
                  They were NOT!

392
00:17:05,859 --> 00:17:09,027
   Well, I MAY have mixed up
    a few ingredients...

393
00:17:09,129 --> 00:17:10,595
             It was such a rush!

394
00:17:10,997 --> 00:17:13,998
  You should both be VERY
  disappointed in yourselves.

395
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,735
      What about YOU and
      your APPLE monster?

396
00:17:17,037 --> 00:17:19,704
       Yes, but you all
       EXPECT that of me..

397
00:17:20,106 --> 00:17:22,640
  All we wanted to do was make
  up for messing things up

398
00:17:22,742 --> 00:17:27,077
  the last time! Sugar Belle,
   Big Mac, we're really-

399
00:17:27,614 --> 00:17:28,546
Where'd they go?

400
00:17:29,816 --> 00:17:33,984
       OK, this time it
       REALLY wasn't me!

401
00:17:35,388 --> 00:17:38,089
   I shouldn't have taken all
    those desserts at once.

402
00:17:38,191 --> 00:17:40,458
   It's just, how can you say
    no to such a sweet idea?

403
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:44,429
   Oh! Ha! Sweet! Haha! I made a joke!

404
00:17:44,731 --> 00:17:47,799
     In retrospect, dragon
     flame and baked goods

405
00:17:47,901 --> 00:17:49,300
     aren't the best combo.

406
00:17:49,502 --> 00:17:51,870
       We felt like it
       was all our fault.

407
00:17:51,972 --> 00:17:53,471
                 Except for the
                  apple monster.

408
00:17:53,773 --> 00:17:55,139
               THAT was Discord.

409
00:17:55,241 --> 00:17:57,342
           And Mrs. Cake messing
           up those recipes..

410
00:17:57,444 --> 00:17:59,710
        And Spike burning the
        messed up recipes. And--

411
00:17:59,812 --> 00:18:02,246
The point is we
ALL felt bad

412
00:18:02,348 --> 00:18:05,316
for ruining Big Mac and
Sugar Belle's proposals!

413
00:18:05,718 --> 00:18:09,821
   It was all green and THEN
   Grand Pear looked at me

414
00:18:09,923 --> 00:18:15,460
 all dramatical and says "where
 NOPONY has gone before"!

415
00:18:15,562 --> 00:18:17,361
   And WHOOSH! Away we flew!

416
00:18:17,463 --> 00:18:20,498
♪♪

417
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,900
                    Today was...
                    interesting.

418
00:18:23,002 --> 00:18:23,668
      Eyup.

419
00:18:24,737 --> 00:18:25,870
                 You OK?

420
00:18:25,972 --> 00:18:26,771
        I...

421
00:18:26,873 --> 00:18:29,674
♪♪

422
00:18:29,776 --> 00:18:31,209
I'm sorry, Sugar Belle.

423
00:18:31,511 --> 00:18:33,812
I wanted everything
to go right today.

424
00:18:34,114 --> 00:18:37,382
   I wanted our love to be as
   perfect as my parents' was

425
00:18:37,484 --> 00:18:39,751
    when they planted these
     two trees together.

426
00:18:40,253 --> 00:18:42,387
Instead, it turned
into a mess.

427
00:18:42,489 --> 00:18:44,155
Just like when I
asked you out,

428
00:18:44,257 --> 00:18:46,557
just like Hearts
and Hooves Day...

429
00:18:46,759 --> 00:18:48,393
         No matter how
          hard I try,

430
00:18:48,495 --> 00:18:51,329
    I always seem to mess
    up when it comes to you.

431
00:18:51,731 --> 00:18:54,899
              I think you've got
              things backwards.

432
00:18:55,001 --> 00:18:55,867
       What do you mean?

433
00:18:56,369 --> 00:18:58,603
    From everything you told
     me about your parents,

434
00:18:58,705 --> 00:19:00,438
     they had to deal with
     things a lot tougher

435
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:03,875
    than some burnt desserts
    and an apple monster.

436
00:19:04,277 --> 00:19:06,277
    I... guess that's true.

437
00:19:06,679 --> 00:19:09,948
  This apple tree and pear
  tree are stronger together.

438
00:19:10,150 --> 00:19:11,983
        They'll survive
        whatever comes

439
00:19:12,085 --> 00:19:14,619
      because they don't
      have to do it <i>alone</i>.

440
00:19:14,721 --> 00:19:18,990
   They BELONG together. Like
   your parents. And like us.

441
00:19:19,192 --> 00:19:20,025
             Eyup.

442
00:19:20,827 --> 00:19:24,395
  Today was a disaster. But
  today was also the last day

443
00:19:24,497 --> 00:19:26,998
    we're ever going to have
    to do anything apart.

444
00:19:27,100 --> 00:19:29,801
       From here on out,
       we'll be together.

445
00:19:30,103 --> 00:19:33,673
 And we'll make sure everything
 always works out just right.

446
00:19:35,275 --> 00:19:36,341
Big Mac will you...
                     Sugar Belle will you...

447
00:19:36,643 --> 00:19:37,742
No, I'm sorry.
                     Sorry.

448
00:19:37,844 --> 00:19:38,909
                  On three?

449
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,444
Sure. One.

450
00:19:40,546 --> 00:19:41,345
                    Two.

451
00:19:41,447 --> 00:19:43,114
    Both: Will you marry me?

452
00:19:43,216 --> 00:19:44,215
          Both: Eyup!

453
00:19:44,717 --> 00:19:49,721
♪♪

454
00:19:49,822 --> 00:19:50,798
        [kiss]

455
00:19:50,923 --> 00:19:52,924
  We'll have to thank our
 friends for messing up so bad

456
00:19:53,026 --> 00:19:55,860
     that they made it all
      work out perfectly.

457
00:19:55,962 --> 00:19:58,897
          [squeaking]

458
00:19:58,999 --> 00:20:02,133
Well, we've ALL made up and
we're here for a do-over.

459
00:20:02,235 --> 00:20:05,103
And this time, thanks to
me, we've got it right!

460
00:20:05,205 --> 00:20:07,838
So, why don't you
two... you know.

461
00:20:07,940 --> 00:20:10,174
               ♪♪

462
00:20:10,276 --> 00:20:13,143
Uh. I think they
did OK without us.

463
00:20:14,747 --> 00:20:16,481
       And THAT'S how we
       were responsible

464
00:20:16,583 --> 00:20:18,449
   for the perfect proposal!

465
00:20:18,551 --> 00:20:21,152
  Heh. Or should I say PAIR-posal!

466
00:20:21,254 --> 00:20:22,987
If we hadn't messed
up so bad...

467
00:20:23,089 --> 00:20:25,323
         It wouldn't have worked
         out the way it did!

468
00:20:25,425 --> 00:20:26,824
It's just
like baking.

469
00:20:26,926 --> 00:20:29,193
Sometimes it's the mistakes
that help you discover

470
00:20:29,295 --> 00:20:31,095
something truly
special.

471
00:20:31,197 --> 00:20:34,198
   And when all the planning
  and grand gestures go wrong,

472
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:36,434
       it reminds you the
      most romantic things

473
00:20:36,536 --> 00:20:38,169
   are usually the simplest.

474
00:20:38,271 --> 00:20:42,106
    Which is what <i>I</i> knew all
    along. You're welcome!

475
00:20:42,208 --> 00:20:44,442
     <i> ♪ [romantic music] ♪</i>

476
00:20:44,544 --> 00:20:55,511
                              ♪♪

477
00:20:55,688 --> 00:20:58,356
        It is my sincere
        pleasure to say,

478
00:20:58,458 --> 00:21:00,659
      for my SECOND Apple
      family wedding,

479
00:21:01,561 --> 00:21:04,595
     that I now pronounce
     you husband and wife.

480
00:21:04,797 --> 00:21:06,997
    You may kiss the bride!

481
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:08,499
            [cheers]

482
00:21:08,601 --> 00:21:10,334
      <i> ♪ [music swells] ♪</i>

483
00:21:10,336 --> 00:21:15,206
               ♪♪

484
00:21:15,308 --> 00:21:16,608
                That's your cue!

485
00:21:17,710 --> 00:21:22,380
<i>♪ Happy marriage, happy apples!</i>
<i>Happy marriage, happy apples! ♪</i>

486
00:21:22,482 --> 00:21:23,514
                     DISCORD!

487
00:21:23,616 --> 00:21:25,650
 Oh, just let me HAVE this one!

488
00:21:26,052 --> 00:21:32,256
<i>♪ Happy marriage, happy apples!</i>
<i>♪ Happy marriage, happy apples!</i>

